For the truly obsessive, or perhaps just those with too much time on their hands, there exist various lists detailing the lives and careers of these judicial figures: a comprehensive [List of all justices](/List_of_justices_of_the_Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States), categorized [by court](/List_of_justices_of_the_Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States_by_court_composition), ranked [by time in office](/List_of_United_States_Supreme_Court_justices_by_time_in_office), organized [by seat](/List_of_justices_of_the_Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States_by_seat), and even a list detailing their academic origins [by education](/List_of_law_schools_attended_by_United_States_Supreme_Court_justices). Separate chronicles exist for the [List of chief justices](/Chief_Justice_of_the_United_States) and the [List of associate justices](/Associate_Justice_of_the_Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States).

